(4)
Company shall include any corporation, partnership, limited liability company,
joint-stock company, joint venture, or association;

(5) Domestic
when applied to corporations shall mean all those created by authority of
this state;

(7)
Foreign when applied to corporations shall include all those created by authority
other than that of this state;

(9)
Grantor shall include every person from or by whom any estate or interest
passes in or by any conveyance;

(10) Inhabitant shall be construed
to mean a resident in the particular locality in reference to which that word
is used;

(11) Land or real estate shall include lands, tenements,
and hereditaments and all rights thereto and interest therein other than a
chattel interest;

(14)
Oath shall include affirmation in all cases in which an affirmation may be
substituted for an oath;

(16) Person shall include bodies politic and
corporate, societies, communities, the public generally, individuals, partnerships,
limited liability companies, joint-stock companies, and associations;

(17)
Personal estate shall include money, goods, chattels, claims, and evidences
of debt;

(19)
Service animal shall have the same meaning as in 28 C.F.R. 36.104, as such
regulation existed on January 1, 2008;

(22) The United
States shall include territories, outlying possessions, and the District of
Columbia;
